Sentencas: The electrochemical behaviour of Ni-based anodes for H+ solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) with a composition consisting of Ni-BaCe0.89Gd0.1Cu0.01O3-5 and Ni-BaCe0.8Y0.2O3-5 was studied.
Titulo: On a variation of the kinetics of hydrogen oxidation on Ni-BaCe(Y,Gd)O3 anode for proton ceramic fuel cells

Sentencas: Ni-BaCe0.8Y0.2O3-5 exhibited poorer performance in comparison with Ni-BaCe0.89Gd0.1Cu0.01O3-5, which was explained by the formation of the BaY2NiO5 phase at the electrode-electrolyte interface during electrode sintering.
Titulo: On a variation of the kinetics of hydrogen oxidation on Ni-BaCe(Y,Gd)O3 anode for proton ceramic fuel cells

Sentencas: It was found that the hydrogen oxidation rate on the Ni-BaCe0.89Gd0.1Cu0.01O3-5 anode in the temperature range of 700 -900 degrees C was determined by the rate of the three stages.
Titulo: On a variation of the kinetics of hydrogen oxidation on Ni-BaCe(Y,Gd)O3 anode for proton ceramic fuel cells

Sentencas: It was shown that the electrode reaction mechanism did not change in this temperature range.
Titulo: On a variation of the kinetics of hydrogen oxidation on Ni-BaCe(Y,Gd)O3 anode for proton ceramic fuel cells

Sentencas: At the temperature of 600 degrees C, the reaction mechanism became more complicated, most likely due to the influence of increased protonic conductivity in the electrolyte.
Titulo: On a variation of the kinetics of hydrogen oxidation on Ni-BaCe(Y,Gd)O3 anode for proton ceramic fuel cells

Sentencas: The nature of the probable ratedetermining stages of hydrogen oxidation is suggested.
Titulo: On a variation of the kinetics of hydrogen oxidation on Ni-BaCe(Y,Gd)O3 anode for proton ceramic fuel cells
